  "title": "@ngrx/component",
  "contents": "\n\n\n  <div class=\"github-links\">\n    <a href=\"https://github.com/ngrx/platform/edit/master/projects/ngrx.io/content/guide/component/index.md?message=docs%3A%20describe%20your%20change...\" aria-label=\"Suggest Edits\" title=\"Suggest Edits\"><i class=\"material-icons\" aria-hidden=\"true\" role=\"img\">mode_edit</i></a>\n  </div>\n\n\n<div class=\"content\">\n<h1 id=\"ngrxcomponent\">@ngrx/component<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/component#ngrxcomponent\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h1>\n<p>Component is a set of primitive reactive helpers to enable fully reactive, fully zone-less applications. They give more control over rendering, and provide further reactivity for Angular applications.</p>\n<div class=\"alert is-critical\">\n<p>This package is experimental and may change during development.</p>\n</div>\n<h2 id=\"key-concepts\">Key Concepts<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/component#key-concepts\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n<p>Rendering happens in the template only:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"guide/component/push\">Push Pipe</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"guide/component/let\">Let Directive</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"installation\">Installation<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/component#installation\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n<p>Detailed installation instructions can be found on the <a href=\"guide/component/install\">Installation</a> page.</p>\n\n</div>\n\n<!-- links to this doc:\n - docs\n-->\n<!-- links from this doc:\n - guide/component#installation\n - guide/component#key-concepts\n - guide/component#ngrxcomponent\n - guide/component/install\n - guide/component/let\n - guide/component/push\n - https://github.com/ngrx/platform/edit/master/projects/ngrx.io/content/guide/component/index.md?message=docs%3A%20describe%20your%20change...\n-->"
}